    "plan_content": "Here's a summary of the plan — ready to implement on your approval.\n\n---\n\n## Plan: Add `ollama rename SOURCE DEST`\n\n**4 source files modified, 0 test files touched.**\n\n### What changes and where\n\n**`api/types.go`** — Add `RenameRequest` struct (mirrors `CopyRequest`) after line 765.\n\n**`api/client.go`** — Add `Rename()` method after `Copy()` (line 387). Uses the same `c.do(ctx, http.MethodPost, \"/api/rename\", ...)` pattern — synchronous, no streaming.\n\n**`server/routes.go`** — Two changes:\n1. **`RenameHandler`** inserted after `CopyHandler` (line 1483). The logic is:\n   - Parse + validate source → **400** if malformed\n   - `manifest.ParseNamedManifest(src)` → **404** if source missing\n   - Parse + validate destination → **400** if malformed\n   - `manifest.ParseNamedManifest(dst)` → **409** if destination already exists\n   - `CopyModel(src, dst)` — copies only the tiny manifest file; blobs are shared by digest, so nothing large is duplicated\n   - `srcManifest.Remove()` only — **`RemoveLayers()` is intentionally skipped** because the destination manifest now references all the same blobs, so nothing is orphaned\n2. **Route** `r.POST(\"/api/rename\", s.RenameHandler)` added alongside `/api/copy` (line 1698)\n\n**`cmd/cmd.go`** — Three changes:\n1. `RenameHandler` function after `CopyHandler` (line 1350) — same shape, prints `renamed 'X' to 'Y'`\n2. `renameCmd` cobra command after `copyCmd` (line 2263) — `Use: \"rename SOURCE DESTINATION\"`, `ExactArgs(2)`, `PreRunE: checkServerHeartbeat`\n3. `renameCmd` added to the env-docs loop and `rootCmd.AddCommand(...)` alongside `copyCmd`\n\n### Key design notes\n- **Same-name rename** (`ollama rename foo foo`) → destination-exists check fires → **409**, no mutation\n- **Blobs are never at risk** — only the manifest file moves; `RemoveLayers` is omitted because it would be a no-op and adds unnecessary filesystem scanning\n- All existing functions (`getExistingName`, `CopyModel`, `manifest.ParseNamedManifest`, `Manifest.Remove`) are reused with no modification",
